    "wordText": "Cut back",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "Cut back",
    "sentenceContext": "Cut back when the choice doesn't align with your values - like, if you're buying a mediocre lunch every day because you haven't made the habit of meal prepping. 如果你的消费选择和自己的价值观不一致，就应该减少这种支出。比如，每天都买一份普普通通的午餐，只因为没有养成提前备餐的习惯。⭐ cut back 削减；减少（雅思高频 phrasal verb）｜align with 与……一致（C1）｜mediocre 普普通通的；一般般的（B2）｜meal prep 提前备餐",
