    "id": "github-cloud-BBC_News___Backlash_after_China_bubble_tea_firm_ordered_to_pay_Louis_Vuitton__1_5m_mp3-13-3-1783405891719",
    "materialId": "github-cloud-BBC_News___Backlash_after_China_bubble_tea_firm_ordered_to_pay_Louis_Vuitton__1_5m_mp3",
    "materialTitle": "BBC News - Backlash after China bubble tea firm ordered to pay Louis Vuitton $1.5m.mp3",
    "subtitleId": 13,
    "wordIndex": 3,
    "wordIndices": [
      3,
      4,
      5,
      6
    ],
    "wordText": "supported the court's verdict",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "support the court's verdict",
    "sentenceContext": "But some online supported the court's verdict.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "不过，也有一些网友支持法院的判决。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ court's verdict —— 法院判决",
    "startTime": 127.16,
    "reviewCount": 1,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-07T06:31:31.719Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "support the court's verdict",
      "ipa": "/səˈpɔːrt ðə kɔːrts ˈvɜːrdɪkt/",
      "translation": "支持法院的裁决",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": "publicly support the court's verdict, refuse to support the court's verdict, support the court's verdict in the case",
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": ""
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**  \n中国学生第一反应可能是“agree with the court's decision”，但“support the verdict”更正式、更法律范儿。Verdict是陪审团或法官的正式裁决，而decision太普通，像在说“我支持食堂今天做宫保鸡丁”。Native speaker在讨论法律案件时，会用verdict来显得专业又严谨。\n\n**2. 学术深度分析与语用场景**  \n“Support the court's verdict”语用上偏中性或褒义，表示对司法结果的认可。常用于社交媒体评论、新闻报道或法律讨论中，比如“But some online supported the court's verdict”就带点“虽然争议大，但有人站法院”的微妙感。感情色彩不戏谑，但如果你用“totally stan the verdict”，那就变饭圈了。\n\n**3. 趣味记忆/联想**  \n谐音梗：verdict = “我滴个天”，想象你听到判决后惊呼“我滴个天，我支持！” 或者联想“very dict”，很权威的dict（话），所以是判决。记住：支持判决，别只说agree，要说support the verdict，瞬间从吃瓜群众变法律达人。"
  },
