    "wordText": "in the outskirts of",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "in the outskirts of",
    "sentenceContext": "Seeing my grandma LaoLao in the outskirts of Beijing and just stay there with her.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "去北京郊区看我的外婆\"姥姥\"，然后陪她住一段时间。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ the outskirts of… ……郊区",
    "startTime": 385.17,
    "reviewCount": 2,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-08T09:12:24.536Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "in the outskirts of",
      "ipa": "/ɪn ðə ˈaʊtskɜːrts əv/",
      "translation": "在……的郊区",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": [
        "in the outskirts of the city",
        "in the outskirts of town",
        "live in the outskirts of",
        "located in the outskirts of"
      ],
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "他们决定在城市的郊区买一栋房子，以便享受更安静的生活。",
          "english": "They decided to buy a house in the outskirts of the city to enjoy a quieter life.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "新机场建在首都的郊区，以缓解市中心的交通压力。",
          "english": "The new airport was built in the outskirts of the capital to relieve (ease) traffic congestion in the city center.",
          "difficulty": "高级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "许多工厂迁移到城市的郊区，因为那里的地价更便宜。",
          "english": "Many factories have relocated to the outskirts of the city because land prices are lower there.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "她小时候住在北京郊区的一个小村庄里，每天骑自行车上学。",
          "english": "When she was a child, she lived in a small village in the outskirts of Beijing and rode (cycled) her bike to school every day.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        }
      ]
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**  \n你可能会说“on the edge of Beijing”或“in the suburb of Beijing”，但native speaker更爱用**in the outskirts**，因为它自带一种“城乡结合部”的荒凉感——不是整齐的suburb，而是有点乱、有点野、可能还有菜地的边缘地带。比如你姥姥住那儿，画面感立刻拉满：土路、平房、鸡叫。  \n\n**2. 学术深度分析**  \n*Outskirts* 源自 *out-*（外）+ *skirt*（裙子边缘），字面“裙摆外沿”，引申为“城市裙边”。语用上略带**疏离感**或**怀旧色彩**，常用于描述非中心、欠发达但有人情味的区域。感情色彩中性偏暖，适合讲故事时营造“远离喧嚣”的氛围。  \n\n**3. 趣味记忆**  \n想象城市是一条裙子，*outskirts*就是裙摆的蕾丝边——好看但容易沾泥。你姥姥住那儿，就像裙摆上的一颗纽扣，虽然偏，但不可或缺。谐音梗：outskirts = “奥特skirts”，奥特曼打小怪兽的郊区，够野！"
  },
