    "wordText": "a shame to",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "be a shame to someone",
    "sentenceContext": "I'm a … I'm a shame to my mum.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "我真是给我妈妈丢脸了。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ be a shame to somebody 让某人觉得丢脸",
    "startTime": 437.783,
    "reviewCount": 1,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-08T09:14:22.114Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "be a shame to someone",
      "ipa": "/biː ə ʃeɪm tə ˈsʌmwʌn/",
      "translation": "让某人蒙羞，使某人丢脸",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": "be a shame to one's family, be a shame to one's parents, feel like a shame to someone",
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "他考试作弊被抓，让全家蒙羞。",
          "english": "He was caught cheating on the exam, which made him a shame to his whole family.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "她觉得自己糟糕的英语水平让父母丢脸。",
          "english": "She felt that her poor English skills were a shame to her parents.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "那个腐败的官员让整个国家蒙羞。",
          "english": "That corrupt official was a shame to the entire nation.",
          "difficulty": "高级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "他因犯罪行为让家族蒙羞，至今无法抬头。",
          "english": "His criminal behavior made him a shame to his family, and he still can't hold his head up.",
          "difficulty": "高级"
        }
      ]
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**中式英语 vs 地道表达**：你第一反应可能是“I'm a shame to my mum”，但native speaker会说“I'm a **disgrace** to my mum”或“I bring shame to my mum”。因为“be a shame”通常指“可惜的事”（如“It's a shame you can't come”），而“be a shame to someone”是中式直译，地道说法用“disgrace”或“bring shame upon”。\n\n**褒贬含义 & 语体**：强烈贬义，口语/非正式，常用于自责或自嘲。\n\n**诙谐记忆**：想象你妈说“You're a shame to me!” 你回“No, Mum, I'm a *shame* to you? That's a shame.” 然后你妈追着你打——记住，**shame**是“可惜”，**disgrace**才是“丢脸”。别让你妈追你！"
  },
