    "wordText": "been thrown into ... chaos of",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "be thrown into ... chaos of",
    "sentenceContext": "And then we've kind of been thrown into this kind of chaos of releasing music and being in the studio and going to gigs, and it's been really, really fun.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "后来我们就一下子投入到发歌、录音、跑演出这样忙碌又混乱的生活中，不过真的特别开心。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ be thrown into 被一下子投入到……｜be in the studio 在录音棚录音｜gig 现场演出｜chaos 忙乱；混乱状态",
    "startTime": 458.765,
    "reviewCount": 1,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-08T09:15:07.236Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "be thrown into ... chaos of",
      "ipa": "/bi θroʊn ˈɪntu ... ˈkeɪɑs əv/",
      "translation": "被抛入……的混乱之中",
      "pronunciationGuide": "注意'be'弱读为/bɪ/；'thrown'中/θ/需咬舌；'into'中/t/在快速语流中可能变为弹舌音；'chaos'读作/ˈkeɪɑs/，重音在第一音节；'of'弱读为/əv/。",
      "collocations": [
        "be thrown into chaos",
        "be thrown into a state of chaos",
        "be thrown into the chaos of war",
        "be thrown into the chaos of daily life"
      ],
      "cefrLevel": "B2",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "to be suddenly forced into a situation that is completely disorganized or confused.",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "当公司突然宣布破产时，所有员工都被抛入了失业的混乱之中。",
          "english": "When the company suddenly declared bankruptcy, all employees were thrown into the chaos of unemployment.",
          "difficulty": "高级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "地震后，整个城市被抛入了救援和重建的混乱之中。",
          "english": "After the earthquake, the entire city was thrown into the chaos of rescue and reconstruction.",
          "difficulty": "高级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "新政策实施后，学校被抛入了课程调整和师资分配的混乱之中。",
          "english": "After the new policy was implemented, the school was thrown into the chaos of curriculum adjustment and teacher allocation.",
          "difficulty": "高级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "他辞职后，团队被抛入了项目管理和任务分配的混乱之中。",
          "english": "After he resigned, the team was thrown into the chaos of project management and task assignment.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        }
      ]
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**  \n你可能会说“I was suddenly very busy with...”，但native speaker用 **be thrown into chaos** 就像被扔进搅拌机——被动、突然、失控感拉满。普通词像白开水，这个表达像冰镇可乐加跳跳糖。\n\n**2. 学术深度分析**  \n**thrown into** 暗示外力强加（如命运、老板），**chaos** 不是普通忙乱，而是“有序宇宙崩塌成混沌”。感情色彩：**戏谑+无奈**，像在说“生活把我丢进滚筒洗衣机，但我还挺享受”。适合吐槽工作、学业、乐队巡演等“甜蜜的负担”。\n\n**3. 趣味记忆**  \n想象你正优雅喝咖啡，突然被一只巨手扔进 **Chaos 大澡堂**，里面全是尖叫的乐谱、吉他线和演出海报。你扑腾着喊：“这澡洗得真带劲！” —— **be thrown into chaos** = 被扔进混乱澡堂，还觉得爽。"
  },
