      "translation": "adj. 冷静的；镇定的；adj. 平静的；镇静的",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": "remain collected and calm; stay collected and calm; appear collected and calm",
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "尽管面临巨大压力，她依然保持冷静沉着，这让整个团队都感到安心。",
          "english": "Despite immense pressure, she remained collected and calm, which reassured the entire team."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "在紧急情况下，医生必须保持冷静沉着，才能做出正确的决定。",
          "english": "In an emergency, a doctor must stay collected and calm to make the right decisions."
