    "wordText": "I hope this doesn't make the final cut",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "I hope this doesn't make the final cut",
    "sentenceContext": "I hope this doesn't make the final cut.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "希望这一段不会被剪进最终版本。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ make the final cut：进入最终剪辑版；最终被保留下来（C1，影视常用）",
    "startTime": 697.283,
    "reviewCount": 2,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-08T09:23:34.052Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "make the final cut",
      "ipa": "/meɪk ðə ˈfaɪnəl kʌt/",
      "translation": "被最终选中；进入最后名单",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": "make the final cut, not make the final cut, hope to make the final cut",
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "导演对这部电影的结局不太满意，担心它可能无法进入最终剪辑版。",
          "english": "The director is not satisfied with the ending of the film and worries it might not make the final cut.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "尽管他表现不错，但由于名额有限，他可能无法进入最终入选名单。",
          "english": "Even though he performed well, due to limited spots, he might not make the final cut.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "在提交简历后，她焦急地等待着是否能够进入面试的最终名单。",
          "english": "After submitting her resume, she anxiously waited to see if she would make the final cut for the interview.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "这个提案虽然很有创意，但预算限制可能导致它无法被最终采纳。",
          "english": "Although the proposal is very creative, budget constraints may cause it not to make the final cut.",
          "difficulty": "高级"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "在激烈的竞争中，只有最优秀的选手才能进入决赛圈。",
          "english": "In fierce competition, only the best contestants can make the final cut.",
          "difficulty": "中级"
        }
      ]
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**\n中国学生第一反应可能是“I hope this won't be chosen at the end”，但老外会说“I hope this doesn't make the final cut”。前者像机器人，后者像电影剪辑师——**“final cut”** 是影视术语，指最终剪辑版。用在这里，瞬间有了导演吐槽自己烂片的幽默感。\n\n**2. 学术深度分析**\n语用上，这句话是**自嘲式谦虚**或**黑色幽默**。比如你刚讲了个冷笑话，补一句“I hope this doesn't make the final cut”，既暗示内容可能很烂，又显得你很有自知之明。感情色彩：**戏谑为主**，偶尔带点真担心。\n\n**3. 趣味记忆**\n想象你是个导演，拍了一部烂片，剪辑时对剪辑师说：“这段别剪进去啊！”——**“final cut”** 就是那个“剪进去”的动作。谐音梗：**“饭呢？砍了！”**（final cut）——饭被砍了，所以没进最终菜单。"
  },
