    "wordText": "Get ... done",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "Get ... done",
    "sentenceContext": "Get my old shopping done on that quid, you idiots. \"",
    "sentenceTranslation": "靠这一镑，我下次买东西的钱都有了，你们这帮傻瓜。\"",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ quid —— 一英镑（英式俚语）｜get…done —— 把……搞定",
    "startTime": 218.487,
    "reviewCount": 1,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-16T07:48:37.879Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "get something done",
      "ipa": "/ɡɛt ˈsʌmθɪŋ dʌn/",
      "translation": "完成某事；让别人做某事",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": [
        "get the work done",
        "get it done",
        "get things done"
      ],
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "我必须在本周末前完成这份报告，否则老板会生气。",
          "english": "I must get this report done by the weekend, or the boss will be angry."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "你能在明天之前把车修好吗？我急需用它。",
          "english": "Can you get the car repaired (fixed up) by tomorrow? I need it urgently."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "她总是能高效地完成任务，因此深受同事尊敬。",
          "english": "She always gets things done efficiently, which earns her great respect from colleagues."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "我们得想办法让这个项目在截止日期前完成。",
          "english": "We need to figure out how to get this project done before the deadline."
        }
      ]
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**  \n你可能会说“I finished my old shopping”，但老外会说“Get my old shopping done”——后者强调**搞定**一件麻烦事，有种“终于甩掉包袱”的爽感。中式英语像白开水，地道表达像冰可乐。  \n\n**2. 学术深度分析与语用场景**  \n“Get something done”是**使役结构**，暗示动作由他人或外力完成，但这里“get done”带点**自嘲式抱怨**：比如你被逼着用优惠券（quid）买完旧货，像完成一项苦差事。感情色彩：**戏谑+无奈**，适合吐槽生活琐事。  \n\n**3. 趣味记忆**  \n想象你是个黑帮老大，对手下吼：“Get that shopping done, you idiots!”——购物像执行任务，**done**就是“搞定收工”。谐音梗：**“搞掂”**（粤语）= get done，瞬间记住！"
  },
  {
    "id": "github-cloud-The_Terrifying_Difference_Between_Night_And_Day_In_The_Countryside_Michael_McIntyre-4-17-1784258436929",
