    ],
    "wordText": "remote ... isolated ... private rolling hills",
    "category": "vocab",
    "customLemma": "remote ... isolated ... private, rolling hills",
    "sentenceContext": "And recently I bought a little place in the countryside for us, beautiful little place, it's very remote, very isolated, very private, rolling hills, it's surrounded by a farm, it's not our farm, but it's just lovely.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "最近，我终于给我们买了一处乡间小屋。那里特别漂亮，位置偏远、与世隔绝、非常私密，四周是连绵起伏的山丘，还被一座农场环绕——虽然农场不是我们的，但整个地方真的美极了。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ remote —— 偏远的｜isolated —— 与世隔绝的｜private —— 清静私密的｜rolling hills —— 连绵起伏的丘陵｜be surrounded by —— 被……环绕",
    "startTime": 18.439,
    "reviewCount": 0,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-17T03:20:36.929Z"
  },
  {
    "id": "github-cloud-The_Terrifying_Difference_Between_Night_And_Day_In_The_Countryside_Michael_McIntyre-6-30-1784258454226",
    "materialId": "github-cloud-The_Terrifying_Difference_Between_Night_And_Day_In_The_Countryside_Michael_McIntyre",
    "materialTitle": "The Terrifying Difference Between Night And Day In The Countryside_Michael McIntyre.mp4",
    "subtitleId": 6,
    "wordIndex": 30,
    "wordText": "giggling",
    "category": "vocab",
    "customLemma": "giggle",
    "sentenceContext": "It was the most magical day when we first moved in, and we were standing outside, all of us, my children, running around in the fields, they couldn't believe it, giggling, and the sun going down, and my wife and I holding hands, going, we did it, it's amazing, I'm so happy, and tears, it was beautiful.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "我们第一次搬进去的那天，是我人生中最梦幻的一天。我们一家人站在屋外，孩子们在田野里跑来跑去，笑个不停，简直不敢相信这一切。夕阳缓缓落下，我和妻子牵着手，不停地说：\"我们做到了，太不可思议了，我太幸福了。\" 我们甚至感动得流下了眼泪，那一刻真的太美好了。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ move in —— 搬进去｜run around —— 跑来跑去｜couldn't believe it —— 简直不敢相信｜giggle —— 咯咯笑｜hold hands —— 牵手",
    "startTime": 30.699,
    "reviewCount": 1,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-17T03:20:54.226Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "giggle",
      "ipa": "/ˈɡɪɡəl/",
      "translation": "v. 咯咯笑，傻笑",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": "giggle nervously, giggle uncontrollably, burst into giggles, a fit of giggles",
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "当老师讲了一个冷笑话时，全班同学都忍不住咯咯笑了起来。",
          "english": "The whole class couldn't help but giggle when the teacher told a lame joke."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "她每次见到偶像都会紧张得咯咯傻笑，像个十几岁的少女。",
          "english": "She would nervously giggle like a teenager every time she saw her idol."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "孩子们在生日派对上收到礼物时，兴奋地咯咯笑个不停。",
          "english": "The children kept giggling with excitement as they received gifts at the birthday party."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "尽管会议很严肃，但那个小失误还是让几位同事偷偷咯咯笑了起来。",
          "english": "Despite the serious meeting, that small mistake made a few colleagues secretly giggle."
        }
      ]
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**  \n中国学生常脱口而出“laugh”或“smile”，但**giggle**特指**压抑的、孩子气的、因兴奋或尴尬而发出的咯咯笑**。比如文中孩子们在田野里奔跑，那种纯真喜悦的“咯咯笑”，用laugh太粗犷，smile太安静，giggle精准捕捉了那种**憋不住、清脆、带点傻气**的快乐。  \n\n**2. 学术深度分析与语用场景**  \nGiggle是**轻量级、高频、非正式**的笑声，常伴随**身体抖动或捂嘴**。感情色彩**积极、可爱**，偶尔带点**戏谑**（比如“She giggled at his joke”暗示笑话有点幼稚）。在专业汇报中慎用，但在口语或文学描写中，它能瞬间营造**温馨、童真**的氛围。  \n\n**3. 趣味记忆/联想**  \n谐音梗：**“咯咯”** 就是中文拟声词，而giggle发音像**“咯咯咯”** 的英文版。想象一只**小鸡**（chick）在**咯咯**笑，拼写也像：**giggle** = **g**（鸡）+ **iggle**（iggle？别管了，记住小鸡咯咯笑就行！）"
  },
  {
    "id": "github-cloud-The_Terrifying_Difference_Between_Night_And_Day_In_The_Countryside_Michael_McIntyre-10-3-1784258484207",
    "materialId": "github-cloud-The_Terrifying_Difference_Between_Night_And_Day_In_The_Countryside_Michael_McIntyre",
