    "wordText": "drifting into",
    "category": "vocab",
    "customLemma": "drift into",
    "sentenceContext": "We're drifting into the neighbour's fields.&nbsp; And foxes.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "我们都快漂到邻居家的田里去了。 还有狐狸。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ drift into… —— 不知不觉偏到……；漂到……",
    "startTime": 131.214,
    "reviewCount": 1,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-17T03:24:51.069Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "drift into",
      "ipa": "/drɪft ˈɪntuː/",
      "translation": "v. 不知不觉地进入（某种状态或情况）",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": [
        "drift into sleep",
        "drift into a conversation",
        "drift into bad habits"
      ],
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "他不知不觉地养成了每天熬夜的习惯。",
          "english": "He drifted into the habit of staying up late every day."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "会议逐渐变成了一场关于预算的激烈争论。",
          "english": "The meeting drifted into a heated argument about the budget."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "她发现自己不知不觉地开始思考人生的意义。",
          "english": "She found herself drifting into thoughts about the meaning of life."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "这个国家在不知不觉中陷入了经济危机。",
          "english": "The country drifted into an economic crisis without anyone noticing."
        }
      ]
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**  \n你可能会说“slowly enter”或“gradually go into”，但 native speaker 用 **drift into** 强调一种**无意识、被动、缓慢**的移动，像被风吹着走。比如“drift into sleep”不是“慢慢睡着”，而是“不知不觉滑入梦乡”。这里说“drift into neighbour's fields”暗示主角**没注意边界**，像漂流一样越界了，比“walk into”更生动。\n\n**2. 学术深度分析**  \n*Drift* 本意是“漂流”，所以 **drift into** 带有**被动、缓慢、甚至有点失控**的语感。感情色彩偏**中性或戏谑**，常用于描述无意的行为或状态变化。比如“drift into a conversation”表示“偶然加入谈话”。在专业汇报中，可以说“The project drifted into a different scope”，暗示范围不知不觉扩大了。\n\n**3. 趣味记忆**  \n想象你是一只**狐狸**（fox），偷偷溜进邻居的鸡舍，不是“跑进去”，而是“飘进去”——**drift into** 就像狐狸的轻手轻脚，加上“and foxes”这个梗，画面感爆棚！谐音梗：**“坠入”** 谐音 **“drift into”**，但“坠”是掉下去，而“drift”是飘着掉，更优雅。"
  },
  {
    "id": "github-cloud-The_Terrifying_Difference_Between_Night_And_Day_In_The_Countryside_Michael_McIntyre-27-25-1784258716604",
    "materialId": "github-cloud-The_Terrifying_Difference_Between_Night_And_Day_In_The_Countryside_Michael_McIntyre",
    "materialTitle": "The Terrifying Difference Between Night And Day In The Countryside_Michael McIntyre.mp4",
    "subtitleId": 27,
    "wordIndex": 25,
    "wordIndices": [
      25,
      27,
      28,
      29
    ],
    "wordText": "disappears ... into thin air",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "disappear into thin air",
    "sentenceContext": "In London, when you see a fox, you see it for a second and you just go, \"Oh, look, there's a fox,\" and then it disappears, like into thin air.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "在伦敦，你看到狐狸时，它通常只出现一秒钟，你说一句\"哦，有只狐狸\"，它就像凭空消失了一样。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ disappear into thin air —— 凭空消失（★★★★★）｜for a second —— 一瞬间",
    "startTime": 137.601,
    "reviewCount": 0,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-17T03:25:16.604Z",
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**  \n中国学生第一反应可能是“disappear suddenly”或“vanish quickly”，但“into thin air”自带魔法特效——仿佛狐狸会隐身术，瞬间蒸发。Native speaker用这个短语时，强调的不是“快”，而是“神秘感”和“不可思议”。\n\n**2. 学术深度分析与语用场景**  \n语用上，它属于**夸张修辞**，常用于描述消失得无影无踪，带点戏谑或惊叹。感情色彩中性偏幽默，适合日常吐槽：“我的钥匙又disappear into thin air了！”——比“I lost my keys”生动十倍。\n\n**3. 趣味记忆**  \n想象狐狸是魔术师，喊一声“Thin Air!”就遁入稀薄空气。谐音梗：“thin air”=“听哪儿？”——你听，它消失了，去哪儿了？空气里！"
  },
