    "wordText": "in my face",
    "category": "idiom",
    "customLemma": "in one's face",
    "sentenceContext": "It was a fox in my face.",
    "sentenceTranslation": "结果一只狐狸就在我眼前。",
    "sentenceVocab": "⭐ in my face —— 就在眼前；贴到脸上（口语）",
    "startTime": 220.923,
    "reviewCount": 1,
    "dateAdded": "2026-07-17T03:30:04.538Z",
    "translationCache": {
      "lemma": "in one's face",
      "ipa": "/ɪn wʌnz feɪs/",
      "translation": "（习语）当面；直接地；公然反对",
      "pronunciationGuide": "",
      "collocations": [
        "throw something in someone's face",
        "laugh in someone's face",
        "slam the door in someone's face"
      ],
      "cefrLevel": "",
      "idiomUsageNote": "",
      "englishDefinition": "",
      "patternPractice": [
        {
          "chinese": "他当着我的面撒谎，我简直不敢相信。",
          "english": "He lied right in my face, and I couldn't believe it."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "她把辞职信甩在我面前，然后头也不回地走了。",
          "english": "She threw the resignation letter in my face and walked away without looking back."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "别在我面前炫耀你的新车了，我知道你买不起。",
          "english": "Stop flaunting your new car in my face; I know you can't afford it."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "他当着所有人的面嘲笑我的提议，让我很尴尬。",
          "english": "He laughed at my proposal in front of everyone, right in my face, which embarrassed me."
        }
      ]
    },
    "teacherExplanation": "**1. 中式英语 vs 地道表达**  \n你第一反应可能是“a fox in front of me”，但“in my face”不是物理距离，而是**扑面而来、猝不及防**的冲击感。就像狐狸突然跳到你脸上，而不是乖乖站在面前。Native speaker用这个词，强调**意外+近距离+视觉冲击**，普通词太温吞了。\n\n**2. 学术深度分析与语用场景**  \n“In one's face”是**习语**，语用上带**戏谑或夸张**色彩。比如“The truth was in my face”指真相**怼脸**，躲都躲不掉。感情色彩偏**生动幽默**，适合口语或叙事，让听众脑补画面。\n\n**3. 趣味记忆**  \n想象一只狐狸**贴脸开大**，你吓得喊“Fox in my face!”——比“There's a fox”刺激100倍。记住：**in your face = 怼脸暴击**，不是“在你面前”的乖乖牌。"
  },
